{
  "stem": "268.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They had to do their own baking and cooking.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they want to bake or pick up a challah or have it sliced yet, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Or rye bread.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was a wonderful cook.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My wife isn't here now.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But I wouldn't-- it wouldn't be a comparison.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] She would bake, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One cake I remember she would bake was a strudel.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In Yiddish it was called a [YIDDISH] strudel.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was-- I was thinking about in Polish it's [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And in English it would be poppy seed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Poppy seed, which is grinded.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she would mix all kind of wonderful stuff in it as a filling.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then they made thin dough and dress it up a little and bake it in the oven.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Oh yeah, we had gas in those days.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Yeah, we had gas.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Where in Czelazd it was a wood-burning stove.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But we already had gas with my mother.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And she knew exactly without timing, without automatic setting and set your cooking time, you know, for buzzing or shutting off the burner.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "All of this was done manually.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And her meat dishes or dairy dishes were delicious.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "She knew how to roast a duck.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And all the other side dishes, which were in Poland in those days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "If you're familiar, they used to call [POLISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] [INAUDIBLE] [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And to clean it was some kind of a job.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And they would spice it and boil it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It was a delicacy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "Or like a salsa, it was called [YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "It was like Jell-O, except it was made out of-- it was a calf's legs.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And they used the Jello-O type.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "It became like a jelly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They would slice it and eat it actually cold.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "It was delicious.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Side dishes, you know, appetizers.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
